title: Final: Dodgers ride Clayton Kershaw back to L.A., beat Mets to force Game 5 Thursday
text: Final: Dodgers ride Clayton Kershaw back to L.A., beat Mets to force Game 5 Thursday Oct. 13, 2015 Updated 8:04 p.m. 1 of 10 The Dodgers' Justin Turner follows through on a double to left field, driving in two runs against the Mets during the third inning Tuesday. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 10 Dodgers pitcher Clayton Kershaw adjusts his cap between pitches against the Mets during the first inning Tuesday. FRANK FRANKLIN II, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 10 The Dodgers' Adrian Gonzalez, right, is greeted by Howie Kendrick after scoring against the Mets during the third inning Tuesday. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 10 Dodgers first baseman Adrian Gonzalez scores on a double to left field by Justin Turner against the Mets during the third inning Tuesday. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 10 The Dodgers' Howie Kendrick (47) is greeted by Yasiel Puig after scoring against the Mets during the third inning Tuesday. FRANK FRANKLIN II, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 10 Mets pitcher Steven Matz, right, talks with David Wright after giving up a two-run double to the Dodgers' Justin Turner during the third inning. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 10 The Dodgers' Justin Turner follows through on a double to left field, driving in two runs against the Mets during the third inning Tuesday. FRANK FRANKLIN II, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 10 Mets pitcher Steven Matz delivers against the Dodgers during the first inning of Game 4 of the National League Division Series on Tuesday. FRANK FRANKLIN II, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 10 The Dodgers' Enrique Hernandez walks back to the dugout after striking out against the Mets during the first inning of Game 4 of the National League Division Series on Tuesday. FRANK FRANKLIN II, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 10 The Mets' Lucas Duda flips his bat after striking out swinging against the Dodgers during the second inning Tuesday. KATHY WILLENS, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS
